cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper deals with adversarial attacks on deep learning models for skeleton-based human action recognition, which involves processing spatio-temporal data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel attack method that involves satisfying multiple physical constraints and employing generative networks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on datasets related to human action recognition, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
